---
import PageFooter from "../components/PageFooter.astro";
import ScrollMorphDiagram from "../components/ScrollMorphDiagram.astro";
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---
<Base title="think — janice quach" description="clarity over cleverness. how janice quach thinks about design, systems, and trade-offs.">
    <div class="bg-layer" id="bgLayer"></div>
    <div class="page">
        <div class="diagram-col">
            <div class="orb orb-a"></div>
            <div class="orb orb-b"></div>
            <ScrollMorphDiagram />
        </div>
        <div class="text-col" id="textCol">
            <section class="text-section" data-section="0">
                <div class="text-inner">
                    <p class="section-num">think</p>
                    <h2>clarity over cleverness</h2>
                    <p>if it needs explaining, it's not clear enough. i believe in principles that compound — simple rules that make every decision after them easier.</p>
                    <p>this is how my brain works. ideas start scattered. the work is finding the structure underneath.</p>
                </div>
            </section>
            <section class="text-section" data-section="1">
                <div class="text-inner">
                    <p class="section-num">01 — structure</p>
                    <h2>structure creates speed</h2>
                    <p>clear systems reduce friction and compound over time. i don't build processes for process sake — i build them because the right structure means the team spends less time navigating and more time making.</p>
                    <p>every decision optimises something and sacrifices something. i'd rather say that out loud than pretend we can have it all.</p>
                </div>
            </section>
            <section class="text-section" data-section="2">
                <div class="text-inner">
                    <p class="section-num">02 — systems</p>
                    <h2>build once, reuse often</h2>
                    <p>solve in ways that scale, not just in ways that ship. the way something is made reflects how much you care about the people using it.</p>
                    <p>i think in systems. not because systems are elegant, but because the right system means the next person doesn't have to solve the same problem again.</p>
                </div>
            </section>
            <section class="text-section" data-section="3">
                <div class="text-inner">
                    <p class="section-num">03 — trade-offs</p>
                    <h2>intentional trade-offs</h2>
                    <p>every decision optimises something and sacrifices something. the honest thing to do is say it out loud — not hide behind "best practice" or pretend trade-offs don't exist.</p>
                    <p>i'd rather make a clear decision with known costs than an unclear one that feels safe.</p>
                </div>
            </section>
            <section class="text-section" data-section="4">
                <div class="text-inner">
                    <p class="section-num">04 — intent</p>
                    <h2>quality reflects intent</h2>
                    <p>the way something is made reflects how much you care about the people using it. every pixel, every interaction, every word — it all communicates care or carelessness.</p>
                    <p>the best work feels obvious. not because it's simple, but because someone made the complexity invisible.</p>
                </div>
            </section>
        </div>
    </div>
    <PageFooter prompt="want to riff on how things should work?" theme="think" />
    <a class="back-btn" href="/">← back</a>
</Base>

<style>
    .back-btn {
        position: fixed;
        top: 2rem;
        left: 2rem;
        z-index: 200;
        font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
        font-size: 0.75rem;
        letter-spacing: 0.15em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: rgba(0,0,0,0.4);
        background: rgba(255,255,255,0.6);
        backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
        border: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.08);
        padding: 0.6rem 1.2rem;
        border-radius: 30px;
        text-decoration: none;
        transition: all 0.3s ease;
    }

    .back-btn:hover {
        color: rgba(0,0,0,0.7);
        background: rgba(255,255,255,0.85);
    }

    .bg-layer {
        position: fixed;
        inset: 0;
        z-index: -1;
        background: #c8d5c0;
        transition: background 0.8s ease;
    }

    .page {
        display: flex;
        min-height: 100vh;
    }

    .diagram-col {
        width: 50%;
        height: 100vh;
        position: sticky;
        top: 0;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
        overflow: hidden;
    }

    .orb-a {
        width: 400px; height: 400px;
        background: radial-gradient(circle at 40% 40%, rgba(168, 190, 140, 0.4), transparent 70%);
        top: -80px; right: -80px;
    }

    .orb-b {
        width: 300px; height: 300px;
        background: radial-gradient(circle at 60% 60%, rgba(200, 220, 180, 0.3), transparent 70%);
        bottom: -60px; left: -40px;
    }

    .text-col {
        width: 50%;
        position: relative;
        z-index: 1;
    }

    .text-section {
        min-height: 100vh;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        padding: 4rem 3rem 4rem 2rem;
    }

    .text-inner { max-width: 440px; }

    .section-num {
        font-size: 0.6rem;
        letter-spacing: 0.2em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: rgba(42, 58, 37, 0.3);
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }

    .text-section h2 {
        font-size: 2.4rem;
        line-height: 1.15;
        margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
        color: #1e2e1a;
    }

    .text-section p {
        font-size: 0.95rem;
        font-weight: 300;
        line-height: 1.85;
        color: #3d4d38;
    }

    .text-section p + p { margin-top: 1rem; }

    @media (max-width: 900px) {
        .page { flex-direction: column; }
        .diagram-col { width: 100%; height: 50vh; }
        .text-col { width: 100%; }
        .text-section { min-height: 80vh; padding: 3rem 2rem; }
    }
</style>
